Verification Summary: b9m3.gcs vs Score PDF
File compiles cleanly with both musicomp2abc and imscomp (only expected "no notes" warnings for unused secondary voices).
CHECK Items Flagged (6 total):
  • Line 379 (m23) & Line 1078 (m63): Score has "piu P" for strings at the "piu P" section, but strings only have vol(p) while winds correctly have vol(pp). Should strings also get
  vol(pp)?
  • Line 417 (m25): Score says "Andante moderato" with tempo marking suggesting ~63 bpm, but GCS has tempo 40,4.
  • Line 732 (m43): Score says "Tempo I (primo)" suggesting return to original tempo (~60), but GCS has tempo 40,4.
  • Line 1115 (m65): Same "Andante moderato" repeat, score suggests ~63, GCS has tempo 45,4.
  • Line 1692 (m99): Score says "Stesso Tempo" (same tempo), GCS has tempo 53,4.
Dynamics Coverage:
  • Overall good: vol(pp), vol(p), vol(mp), vol(mf), vol(f), vol(ff), vol(sf) all used appropriately
  • Crescendo/decrescendo (vol<, vol>) markings present for "cres" and "dim:" passages
  • FF climax sections (m147, m132, m122) correctly have vol(ff)
  • sF markings on Horns and Trumpets (m122, m132) correctly have vol(sf)
  • Final measure (m157) correctly has mp -> f -> pp ending
Expression Markings NOT Captured (consistent throughout file):
  • "dol." / "dolce" - sweetly (appears as comments only)
  • "Cantabile" - singing style
  • "espressione" - with expression
  • "morendo" - dying away
  • "pizz." / "arco" - string techniques
  • "Col B." - colla parte marking
  • "cres poco a poco" - gradual crescendo (represented by vol<)
Key/Time Signatures Verified:
  • B-flat major (initial) -> D major (m25) -> B-flat major (m43) -> D major (m65) -> B-flat major (m83) -> all correct
  • 12/8 sections (m93+) correct
  • Time signature changes verified
Score Page 95:
  • Missing from PDF (gap between pages 94 and 96/Movement 4)
  • GCS has m152-157 on page 95 - cannot be verified against score
The tempo discrepancies are the most significant findings. They may be intentional artistic choices by the transcriber (slower tempos for a particular interpretation), but are
flagged for review.
